          "_name": "header13",
          "_sourceTheme": "startm5",
          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"header13\" group=\"Headers\" data-bg-video=\"{{bg.type == 'video' && bg.value.url}}\" mbr-class=\"{\n    'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen,\n    'mbr-parallax-background': bg.parallax}\">\n  <mbr-parameters>\n    <header>Size</header>\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Screen\" name=\"fullScreen\">\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Width\" name=\"fullWidth\">\n    <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"12\" step=\"1\" value=\"6\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n    <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"12\" step=\"1\" value=\"6\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n    <input type=\"range\" name=\"imageWidth\" title=\"Image Width\" min=\"1\" max=\"12\" step=\"1\" value=\"8\" condition=\"showImage\">\n    <header>Show/Hide</header>\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Title\" name=\"showTitle\" checked>\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Text\" name=\"showText\" checked>\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Buttons\" name=\"showButtons\">\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Image\" name=\"showImage\" checked>\n    <header>Background</header>\n    <fieldset type=\"background\" name=\"bg\" parallax>\n      <input type=\"image\" title=\"Image\" value=\"../_images/background1.jpg\" parallax>\n      <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" value=\"#edefeb\" selected>\n      <input type=\"video\" title=\"Video\" value=\"https://vimeo.com/428046504\">\n    </fieldset>\n    <header condition=\"bg.type === 'video'\">Fallback Image</header>\n    <input type=\"image\" title=\"Fallback Image\" value=\"../_images/background1.jpg\" name=\"fallBackImage\" condition=\"bg.type === 'video'\">\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Overlay\" name=\"overlay\" condition=\"bg.type !== 'color'\">\n    <input type=\"color\" title=\"Overlay Color\" name=\"overlayColor\" value=\"#ffffff\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n    <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Opacity\" name=\"overlayOpacity\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"0.5\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n  </mbr-parameters>\n\n  <div class=\"mbr-fallback-image disabled\" mbr-if=\"bg.type == 'video'\"></div>\n  <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\" opacity=\"{{overlayOpacity}}\" bg-color=\"{{overlayColor}}\"></div>\n\n  <div class=\"align-center\" mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n    <div class=\"row justify-content-center\" mbr-if=\"showTitle || showText || showButtons\">\n      <div class=\"col-md-12 mb-5 content-head\">\n        <h1 class=\"mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-title\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-1\" mbr-if=\"showTitle\"><b>How to Land a Job in South Africa in 30 Days or Less</b></h1>\n        <p class=\"mbr-text mbr-fonts-style mt-4\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\" mbr-if=\"showText\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text, .mbr-section-btn\">\n          Finding a job in South Africa can be overwhelming, especially if you're on a tight deadline. However, with the right strategy, tools, and focus, it's possible to secure a job in 30 days or less. This guide is tailored for South African job seekers who desire real results. Whether you're a recent graduate, someone who has been retrenched, or an individual returning to the workforce, this plan is effective if you commit to it. We'll break it down into weekly goals, daily actions, and insider tips that will enhance your chances of success.\n        </p>\n        <div mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" class=\"mbr-section-btn mt-4\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnMove\">\n          <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"https://mobiri.se\" data-app-placeholder=\"Type Text\">Create Free Website!</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\n      <div class=\"col-12 col-md-{{imageWidth}}\" mbr-if=\"showImage\">\n        <img src=\"@PROJECT_PATH@/assets/images/mbr-1695x1130.jpg\" alt=\"Mobirise Website Builder\" title>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>",
          "_cid": "v5zpGk8EoJ",
          "_anchor": "header13-2r",
          "_protectedParams": [],
          "_global": false,
          "_once": false,
          "_params": {}
        },
        {
          "alias": false,
          "_styles": {
            "padding-top": "(@paddingTop * 1rem)",
            "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 1rem)",
            "background-color": "@bgColor",
            ".mbr-text": {
              "color": "#000000"
            },
            ".mbr-section-subtitle": {
              "color": "#000000"
            },
            ".mbr-section-title": {
              "color": "#000000"
            }
          },
          "_name": "article12",
          "_sourceTheme": "startm5",
          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"article12\" group=\"Article\">    \n    <mbr-parameters>\n        <header>Size</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Width\" name=\"fullWidth\" checked>\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"2\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\">\n        <input type=\"range\" name=\"textWidth\" title=\"Width\" min=\"4\" max=\"12\" value=\"12\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Show/Hide</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Title\" name=\"showTitle\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Subtitle\" name=\"showSubtitle\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Text\" name=\"showText\" checked>\n        <header>Background</header>\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\">\n    </mbr-parameters>\n    <div mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n        <div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12 col-lg-{{textWidth}}\">\n                <h3 class=\"mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4 mt-0\" mbr-if=\"showTitle\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-title\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-2\">\n                <b>Framing time</b>\n                </h3>\n                <h4 class=\"mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-if=\"showSubtitle\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-5\">The storytelling magic of photos\n                </h4>\n                <p class=\"mbr-text mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-if=\"showText\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\"><b>Week 1: Set Up for Success\n</b><br>\n<br><b>1. Polish Your CV and Cover Letter</b><br><b>\n</b><br>Your CV is your first impression. Use a professional South African CV template. Highlight achievements, not just duties. Use strong action words like \"implemented,\" \"managed,\" and \"increased.\" Focus on measurable results. Ensure it aligns with the job you are applying for. Utilize JobFinds' CV resources for assistance.\n<br>Write a tailored cover letter for each application. Address it to the hiring manager if possible. Use the employer’s name, the specific job title, and explain why you’re the best fit. Ensure it aligns with the job you are applying for. Utilize JobFinds' CV resources for assistance.<br><br><b>2. Create a Powerful LinkedIn Profile\n</b><br>Recruiters in South Africa are actively using LinkedIn. To improve your profile, ensure your headline includes the key job titles you are targeting. Write a strong 'About' section and list all relevant skills. Upload a professional photo, and consider adding a custom banner. If applicable, include links to your CV or portfolio.\n<br>\n<br>Ask colleagues or former managers to endorse your skills and provide recommendations to enhance your credibility. Use the Featured section to showcase past projects, certificates, or a visual CV.\n<br>\n<br><b>3. Register on Major Job Portals\n</b><br>Create accounts and upload your CV on:\n<br>• JobFinds\n<br>• PNet\n<br>• Careers24\n<br>• Indeed South Africa\n<br>• LinkedIn Jobs\n<br>\n<br><b>Enable job alerts for your keywords. Set filters to your preferred location, industry, and salary. Some portals even allow you to set availability status to “Immediately available.”\n</b><br>\n<br><b>4. Define Your Job Targets\n</b><br>Don’t apply to every role. Get specific:\n<br>Job titles: e.g., HR Officer, IT Recruiter, Admin Clerk\n<br>Location: Johannesburg, Cape Town, Durban, or remote\n<br>Salary expectations\n<br>Preferred company size and culture\n<br>This helps you customise your applications and track results.\n<br>\n<br><b>Week 2: Strategic Job Applications\n</b><br>\n<br><b>5. Apply to 5–10 Jobs Daily (Targeted)\n</b><br>Customize your CV for each job application by using relevant keywords from the job description. Maintain a spreadsheet to track your applications, which should include the company name, role, date applied, contact person, and any feedback received.&nbsp;<br><br>Consider automating this process with tools like Huntr or Jobjack's job tracking board. Additionally, it's wise to keep backups of different versions of your CV. Organize them into folders labeled \"CV for Admin Jobs,\" \"CV for Recruitment,\" and so on.\n<br>\n<br><b>6. Use LinkedIn to Connect and Message Recruiters\n</b><br>Send personalised connection requests. After they accept, thank them and express interest in current opportunities. Keep it brief and professional. Avoid sounding desperate—focus on adding value.\n<br>Sample message: “Hi [Name], I admire your work at [Company]. I’m actively exploring new opportunities in [field] and would appreciate staying connected. Please let me know if there’s any advice or openings I should know about.”\n<br><br><b>7. Apply on Company Websites\n</b><br>Go beyond portals. Visit career pages of companies you admire and apply directly. This shows initiative. Use Google with terms like: “site:companyname.co.za careers” or “jobs at [company name] South Africa.”\n<br>Make a list of 20 dream companies and schedule weekly visits to their websites.\n<br>\n<br><b>8. Clean Up Your Social Media\n</b><br>Employers often check Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram. Remove anything unprofessional or controversial. Create a personal brand online by posting job search progress, volunteer work, or helpful career tips. Follow recruitment pages and job boards.\n<br>\n<br><b>Week 3: Interview Preparation and Visibility Boost\n</b><br>\n<b><br>9. Practice Interview Questions\n</b><br>Prepare for both virtual and in-person interviews by utilizing platforms like Glassdoor to find sample interview questions relevant to your desired roles.\n<br>\n<b><br>Common Questions to Expect:\n</b><br>- Tell me about yourself.\n<br>- Why should we hire you?\n<br>- What are your strengths and weaknesses?\n<br>- Can you recall a time at work when you faced a challenging problem?\n<br>\n<br>To practice, record yourself answering these questions, timing your responses. Focus on maintaining good posture and eye contact. If you are preparing for a virtual interview, ensure you test your technology in advance.<br>\n<b><br>10. Post Content on LinkedIn\n</b><br>Share relevant career advice, your journey, or insights into your industry. Comment on other posts to stay visible. Posting consistently improves your chances of being discovered by recruiters, as well as finding jobs posted by hiring companies/ recruiters. The algorithm is there, when LinkedIn picks up that you are jobhunting, you will receive more job posts.<br>\n<br><b>Topics to post:\n</b><br>• Lessons from your job search\n<br>• Career goals\n<br>• Your updated CV or portfolio\n<br>• Industry news and thoughts\n<br>• Free tools or job hunting hacks\n<br>\n<br><b>11. Get a Reference Letter\n</b><br>Ask previous employers or colleagues for a reference. A strong reference can speed up your chances of landing a job. Offer them a sample letter to make it easier for them. If you’ve volunteered or freelanced, those also count.\n<br>\n<br><b>12. Prepare Interview Outfits\n</b><br>Dress codes vary, but always lean professional. Have at least one interview-ready outfit clean and pressed. Make sure it fits well and makes you feel confident. Also test your lighting and background if you’ll be doing virtual interviews. Don’t forget to groom yourself properly—it adds to your professional appearance.\n<br>\n<br><b>Week 4: Follow Ups and Final Push\n</b><br>\n<br><b>13. Follow Up on Applications\n</b><br>**Follow-Up Email Guidelines**\n<br>1. Wait 5–7 days after your initial application before sending a follow-up email.\n<br>2. Reaffirm your interest in the position and highlight one skill or experience that aligns well with the role.\n<br>Discover more\n<br>Software\n<br>Science\n<br>email\n<br>communication skills\n<br>software\n<br>Communication\n<br>emails\n<br>communication\n<br>JobFinds\n<br>Email\n<br>\n<br><b>3. Keep your email concise—no longer than 4 sentences.</b><br>**Subject:** Follow-Up on [Job Title] Application\n<br>**Body:**\n<br>“Dear [Recruiter Name/ Company],\n<br>I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to follow up on my application for the [Position] and express my continued interest. I believe my [specific skill or experience] would be a great fit for this role. Please let me know if you need any additional information.”\n<br>\n<br><b>14. Attend Career Fairs and Networking Events\n</b><br>Virtual or in-person, these events are goldmines. Prepare your elevator pitch and carry your printed CV. Bring business cards if possible. Introduce yourself confidently and make connections beyond recruiters—speak to fellow job seekers too.\n<br>Sites like Eventbrite, Facebook Events, and JobFinds often list free or low-cost career expos and workshops.\n<br>\n<br><b>15. Keep Momentum\n</b><br>If you're not seeing traction, review your CV, apply to different industries, or seek mentorship from someone in your field. Take free online courses to upskill with platforms like:\n<br>\n<br>• Coursera\n<br>• LinkedIn Learning\n<br>• Skills Portal\n<br>• Udemy (free courses or specials)\n<br>• Create a portfolio of completed work—even if it’s from a mock project. Show your skills in action.\n<br>\n<br><b>16. Prepare for Job Offers\n</b><br>Research fair salary ranges. Know your value. Be ready to accept or negotiate with confidence. Don’t rush—ask for time to review an offer if needed. Compare benefits, location, and growth potential.\n<br>Discover more\n<br>Communication\n<br>Software\n<br>Science\n<br>Email\n<br>JobFinds\n<br>communication\n<br>LinkedIn\n<br>communication skills\n<br>emails\n<br>messaging\n<br>\n<br><b>Understand the terms in your contract. Clarify probation periods, notice periods, deductions, and perks. If unsure, seek advice from a recruiter or HR friend.\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Bonus Tips:</b><br>• Use tools like Grammarly to proofread your applications.\n<br>• Don’t ghost recruiters – always respond, even if you decline.\n<br>• Treat job hunting like a job: consistent hours, goals, and discipline.\n<br>• Use a professional email address (e.g., yourname@gmail.com or @jobfinds.co.za)\n<br>• Set daily intentions and affirmations to stay focused.\n<br>• Join online forums like Reddit ZAJobs or Facebook groups for job seekers.\n<br>• Stay physically active and eat well to maintain energy and positivity.\n<br>\n<br>Job hunting in South Africa is competitive, but with this focused 30-day plan, you have a real shot at landing your next opportunity. Stick to the steps, stay confident, and remember: you only need one \"yes.\" Don’t let discouragement steal your momentum.<br>\n<br>Your future employer might already be reading your CV—so give them something to say yes to. For CV templates, job listings, and career tools, explore JobFinds today.\n<br>\n<br>Your next job is already looking for you—go find it.\n<br>\n<br><b>Other Article:</b> <a href=\"page18.html\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">Job-Hunting Success Kit</a><br></p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
