              "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 1rem)",
              ".carousel": {
                "height": "800px",
                "img": {
                  "width": "100%",
                  "height": "100%",
                  "object-fit": "cover"
                }
              },
              ".carousel-item, .carousel-inner": {
                "height": "100%"
              }
            },
            "& when (@fullScreen)": {
              "padding-top": "0",
              "padding-bottom": "0",
              ".carousel": {
                "width": "100%"
              },
              ".carousel-inner": {
                "display": "flex",
                "align-content": "center",
                "align-items": "center"
              },
              ".carousel-item img": {
                "height": "100vh",
                "object-fit": "cover"
              }
            },
            "img, .item-wrapper": {
              "border-radius": "0 !important"
            },
            ".carousel-caption": {
              "bottom": "40px",
              "z-index": "1"
            },
            ".mobi-mbri-arrow-next": {
              "margin-left": "5px"
            },
            ".mobi-mbri-arrow-prev": {
              "margin-right": "5px"
            },
            ".carousel-control:hover": {
              "background": "#1b1b1b",
              "color": "#fff",
              "opacity": "1"
            },
            ".item-wrapper": {
              "width": "100%"
            },
            "@media (max-width: 767px)": {
              ".container .carousel-control": {
                "margin-bottom": "0"
              },
              ".content-slider-wrap": {
                "width": "100% !important"
              }
            },
            ".container .carousel-indicators": {
              "margin-bottom": "3px"
            },
            ".carousel-control": {
              "top": "50%",
              "width": "60px",
              "height": "60px",
              "margin-top": "-1.5rem",
              "font-size": "22px",
              "background-color": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)",
              "border": "2px solid #fff",
              "border-radius": "50%",
              "transition": "all 0.3s",
              "&.carousel-control-prev": {
                "left": "0",
                "margin-left": "2.5rem"
              },
              "&.carousel-control-next": {
                "right": "0",
                "margin-right": "2.5rem"
              },
              "@media (max-width: 767px)": {
                "top": "auto",
                "bottom": "1rem"
              }
            },
            ".carousel-indicators": {
              "position": "absolute",
              "bottom": "0",
              "margin-bottom": "1.5rem !important",
              "li": {
                "max-width": "15px",
                "height": "15px",
                "width": "15px",
                "max-height": "15px",
                "margin": "3px",
                "background-color": "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)",
                "border": "2px solid #fff",
                "border-radius": "50%",
                "opacity": "0.5",
                "transition": "all 0.3s",
                "&.active, &:hover": {
                  "opacity": "0.9"
                },
                "&::after, &::before": {
                  "content": "none"
                }
              },
              "&.ie-fix": {
                "left": "50%",
                "display": "block",
                "width": "60%",
                "margin-left": "-30%",
                "text-align": "center"
              },
              "@media (max-width: 768px)": {
                "display": "none !important"
              }
            },
            ".mbr-section-subtitle, .mbr-section-text, .mbr-section-btn": {
              "@media (max-width: 991px)": {
                "text-align": "center"
              }
            },
            "& when not (@showArrows)": {
              ".carousel-control-prev, .carousel-control-next": {
                "display": "none"
              }
            }
          },
          "_name": "slider03",
          "_sourceTheme": "startm5",
          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"slider3\" group=\"Gallery & Slider\" mbr-class=\"{'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen}\">\n    <mbr-parameters>\n        <input type=\"id\" name=\"sliderId\">\n        <header>Size</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Screen\" name=\"fullScreen\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"0\" condition=\"!fullScreen\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"0\" condition=\"!fullScreen\">\n        <header>Carousel</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Fade Effect\" name=\"fade\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Autoplay\" name=\"autoplay\">\n        <input type=\"range\" title=\"Interval\" name=\"interval\" min=\"3\" max=\"10\" value=\"5\" step=\"1\" condition=\"autoplay\">\n        <header>Slide</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Caption\" name=\"showCaption\" checked>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Text\" name=\"showText\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Button\" name=\"showButtons\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Bullets\" name=\"showBullets\" checked>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Arrows\" name=\"showArrows\" checked>\n        <header>Background</header>\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\" selected>\n    </mbr-parameters>\n    <div id=\"{{sliderId}}\" class=\"carousel slide\" mbr-class=\"{'carousel-fade': fade}\" data-ride=\"{{autoplay ? 'carousel' : false}}\" data-bs-ride=\"{{autoplay ? 'carousel' : false}}\" data-interval=\"{{interval*1000}}\" data-bs-interval=\"{{interval*1000}}\">\n        <ol class=\"carousel-indicators\" mbr-if=\"showBullets\">\n            <li data-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-bs-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-slide-to=\"0\" data-bs-slide-to=\"0\" class=\"active\"></li>\n            <li data-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-bs-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-slide-to=\"1\" data-bs-slide-to=\"1\"></li>\n            <li data-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-bs-target=\"#{{sliderId}}\" data-slide-to=\"2\" data-bs-slide-to=\"2\"></li>\n        </ol>\n        <div class=\"carousel-inner\">\n            <div class=\"carousel-item slider-image item active\">\n                <div class=\"item-wrapper\">\n                    <img class=\"d-block w-100\" src=\"@PROJECT_PATH@/assets/images/mbr-3-1800x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Mobirise Website Builder\">\n                    <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay\" mbr-style=\"{'opacity': overlayOpacity, 'background-color': overlayColor}\">\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"carousel-caption\" mbr-if=\"showCaption || showText || showButtons\">\n                        <h5 class=\"mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-3\" mbr-if=\"showCaption\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-1\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\"><b>Beginner’s guide to freelancing in South Africa&nbsp;</b></h5>\n                        <p class=\"mbr-section-text mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-if=\"showText\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-text, .mbr-section-btn\">Embarking on the journey of starting a business can be a daunting endeavor, particularly when financial constraints loom large. In South Africa, many aspiring entrepreneurs are led to believe that a hefty capital of R50,000 or more is necessary before they can even entertain the idea of launching their own venture. However, the reality is both liberating and encouraging: you can ignite a small, thriving business with a mere R1,000, provided you select the right concept and strategy.</p>\n                        <div mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" class=\"mbr-section-btn mb-5\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnAdd, -mbrBtnMove, -mbrBtnRemove\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"https://mobiri.se\" data-app-placeholder=\"Type Text\">Get started</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>     \n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"carousel-item slider-image item\">\n                <div class=\"item-wrapper\">\n                    <img class=\"d-block w-100\" src=\"@PROJECT_PATH@/assets/images/mbr-612x361.webp\" alt=\"Mobirise Website Builder\">\n                    <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay\" mbr-style=\"{'opacity': overlayOpacity, 'background-color': overlayColor}\">\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"carousel-caption\" mbr-if=\"showCaption || showText || showButtons\">\n                        <h5 class=\"mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-3\" mbr-if=\"showCaption\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-1\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\"><b>Beginner’s guide to freelancing in South Africa&nbsp;</b></h5>\n                        <p class=\"mbr-section-text mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-if=\"showText\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-text, .mbr-section-btn\">Embarking on the journey of starting a business can be a daunting endeavor, particularly when financial constraints loom large. In South Africa, many aspiring entrepreneurs are led to believe that a hefty capital of R50,000 or more is necessary before they can even entertain the idea of launching their own venture. However, the reality is both liberating and encouraging: you can ignite a small, thriving business with a mere R1,000, provided you select the right concept and strategy.</p>\n                        <div mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" class=\"mbr-section-btn mb-5\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnAdd, -mbrBtnMove, -mbrBtnRemove\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"https://mobiri.se\" data-app-placeholder=\"Type Text\">Get started</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>     \n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"carousel-item slider-image item\">\n                <div class=\"item-wrapper\">\n                    <img class=\"d-block w-100\" src=\"@PROJECT_PATH@/assets/images/mbr-596x397.webp\" alt=\"Mobirise Website Builder\">\n                    <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay\" mbr-style=\"{'opacity': overlayOpacity, 'background-color': overlayColor}\">\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"carousel-caption\" mbr-if=\"showCaption || showText || showButtons\">\n                        <h5 class=\"mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-3\" mbr-if=\"showCaption\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-1\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\"><b>Beginner’s guide to freelancing in South Africa&nbsp;</b></h5>\n                        <p class=\"mbr-section-text mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-if=\"showText\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-text, .mbr-section-btn\">Embarking on the journey of starting a business can be a daunting endeavor, particularly when financial constraints loom large. In South Africa, many aspiring entrepreneurs are led to believe that a hefty capital of R50,000 or more is necessary before they can even entertain the idea of launching their own venture. However, the reality is both liberating and encouraging: you can ignite a small, thriving business with a mere R1,000, provided you select the right concept and strategy.</p>\n                        <div mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" class=\"mbr-section-btn mb-5\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnAdd, -mbrBtnMove, -mbrBtnRemove\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"https://mobiri.se\" data-app-placeholder=\"Type Text\">Get started</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>     \n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <a class=\"carousel-control carousel-control-prev\" href=\"#{{sliderId}}\" role=\"button\" data-slide=\"prev\" data-bs-slide=\"prev\">\n            <span class=\"mobi-mbri mobi-mbri-arrow-prev\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n            <span class=\"sr-only visually-hidden\">Previous</span>\n        </a>\n        <a class=\"carousel-control carousel-control-next\" href=\"#{{sliderId}}\" role=\"button\" data-slide=\"next\" data-bs-slide=\"next\">\n            <span class=\"mobi-mbri mobi-mbri-arrow-next\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n            <span class=\"sr-only visually-hidden\">Next</span>\n        </a>\n    </div>\n</section>",
          "_cid": "v5KaOIaXSs",
          "_anchor": "slider03-3d",
          "_protectedParams": [],
          "_global": false,
          "_once": false,
          "_params": {}
        },
        {
          "alias": false,
          "_styles": {
            "padding-top": "(@paddingTop * 1rem)",
            "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 1rem)",
            "background-color": "@bgColor",
            ".mbr-text": {
              "color": "#000000"
            },
            ".mbr-section-subtitle": {
              "color": "#000000"
            },
            ".mbr-section-title": {
              "color": "#000000"
            }
          },
          "_name": "article12",
          "_sourceTheme": "startm5",
          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"article12\" group=\"Article\">    \n    <mbr-parameters>\n        <header>Size</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Width\" name=\"fullWidth\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\">\n        <input type=\"range\" name=\"textWidth\" title=\"Width\" min=\"4\" max=\"12\" value=\"12\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Show/Hide</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Title\" name=\"showTitle\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Subtitle\" name=\"showSubtitle\" checked>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Text\" name=\"showText\" checked>\n        <header>Background</header>\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\">\n    </mbr-parameters>\n    <div mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n        <div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12 col-lg-{{textWidth}}\">\n                <h3 class=\"mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4 mt-0\" mbr-if=\"showTitle\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-title\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-2\">\n                <b>Framing time</b>\n                </h3>\n                <h4 class=\"mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-if=\"showSubtitle\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\"><b>Freelancing has emerged from the shadows to become a vibrant and dynamic career choice in South Africa. Amidst soaring unemployment rates and escalating living expenses, an increasing number of South Africans are embarking on a freelancing journey as a means to secure financial stability, cultivate independence, and tap into lucrative opportunities with international clients who pay in dollars, pounds, or euros.<br><br>\n</b><div>\n</div><div><b>\n</b></div><div><b>This comprehensive beginner’s guide is crafted specifically for South Africans eager to dive into the world of freelancing but unsure of how to navigate the waters. You’ll discover the essence of freelancing, uncover the skills that are currently in high demand, learn the art of crafting an appealing profile, find the best channels to connect with clients, and master the strategies for positioning yourself as a standout freelancer in 2025. Get ready to transform your career path and seize the opportunities that await!</b></div></h4>\n                <p class=\"mbr-text mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-if=\"showText\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\"><b>What is Freelancing?\n</b><br>Freelancing presents a dynamic and flexible way of working, allowing individuals to offer their expertise to clients on a contract or project basis rather than adhering to the traditional permanent employment model. As a freelancer, you're not just an employee; you are your own boss, empowered to choose the clients you collaborate with, define your own rates, and curate your workload to fit your lifestyle and goals.\n<br>\n<br>This model goes beyond merely being a side hustle; with a strategic approach, freelancing can evolve into a rewarding full-time career. In South Africa, many embrace freelancing as a means to enhance their income, while others transform it into thriving six-figure annual careers, meticulously crafting their success through passion and skill. Whether you're diving into freelancing for supplemental income or aiming to build a substantial career, the possibilities are as vast as your ambition.\n<br>\n<br><b>Why Freelancing is Growing in South Africa\n</b><br>\n<br>High Unemployment: In today's economy, where permanent job opportunities seem scarce, freelancing emerges as a beacon of hope, offering a viable path to financial stability.\n<br>\n<br>Global Demand: Businesses across the globe are actively seeking talented remote freelancers in fields like writing, graphic design, information technology, and customer support, breaking down geographical barriers and creating a vibrant marketplace for skills.\n<br>\n<br>Currency Advantage: Imagine earning $500 on Upwork, a sum that converts into nearly R9,000 locally, allowing you to stretch your earnings further in your home country.\n<br>\n<br>Flexibility: With freelancing, you hold the reins—select your projects and set your own schedule, enabling you to create a work-life balance that suits your lifestyle and aspirations.\n<br>\n<br>Low Startup Costs: Embarking on this freelance journey requires minimal investment; all you need is a reliable laptop, a stable internet connection, and the right skillset to launch your career into exciting new territories.\n<br>\n<br>Skills in Demand for Freelancers\n<br>\n<br><b>Not sure where you fit in? Here are the top categories hiring South Africans in 2026:\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Writing &amp; Editing</b> – Crafting engaging blogs, polished website copy, and meticulously detailed technical writing that captivates and informs.\n<br><b>Virtual Assistance</b> – Seamlessly handling administrative tasks, expertly managing schedules, and efficiently conducting data entry to keep operations running smoothly.\n<br><b>Graphic Design</b> – Designing striking logos, creating cohesive branding elements, and producing eye-catching social media visuals that resonate and inspire.\n<br><b>Web Development </b>– Building robust WordPress sites and dynamic e-commerce platforms that deliver an exceptional user experience and drive online success.\n<br><b>Social Media Management</b> – Curating thoughtful content calendars and executing targeted paid ad campaigns that amplify brand presence and engage audiences.\n<br><b>Tutoring &amp; Teaching </b>– Providing personalized English tutoring and specialized subject help that empowers learners and enhances their understanding.\n<br><b>Transcription &amp; Translation</b> – Converting audio to text with precision and offering seamless multilingual translations that bridge communication gaps.\n<br><b>SEO &amp; Digital Marketing</b> – Conducting in-depth keyword research, optimizing Google Ads, and orchestrating compelling email campaigns that elevate online visibility and outreach.\n<br><b>Customer Service </b>– Delivering top-notch chat or email support for global companies, ensuring customer satisfaction and fostering lasting relationships.\n<br><b>Video &amp; Audio Editing</b> – Polishing YouTube videos, refining podcast episodes, and curating TikTok content to produce engaging narratives that captivate viewers.\n<br>\n<br>👉 Pro Tip: Choose a single skill to master, then transform it into a niche. For instance, rather than simply identifying yourself as a “writer,” position yourself as a “health and wellness blog writer,” painting a clear picture of your expertise in the vibrant world of holistic living and personal well-being.\n<br>\n<br><b>Step-by-Step: How to Start Freelancing in South Africa</b><br><b>\n</b><br><b>Step 1: Pick Your Freelance Skill\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Think about:</b><br><b>\n<br>Step 1: Discover Your Unique Value Proposition\n</b><br>Take a moment to reflect on your existing skills — whether it's your knack for administration, your flair for design, or your talent for engaging writing. Consider what truly sparks joy within you; what activities make your heart race with excitement? Additionally, think about what others perceive as valuable enough to invest their resources in.\n<br>\n<br>If you’re just starting out, the digital landscape offers a wealth of learning opportunities. Platforms like Google Digital Skills, HubSpot Academy, and countless tutorials on YouTube provide accessible routes to acquire vital skills without spending a dime.\n<br>\n<b><br>Step 2: Create a Straightforward Portfolio\n</b><br>As you embark on this journey, remember that clients seek tangible evidence of your abilities. A portfolio serves as a curated showcase of your best work; it doesn't have to be elaborate or extravagant at the outset. Instead, let it reflect your capabilities and promise, giving potential clients confidence in your ability to deliver exceptional results.\n<br>\n<br><b>Options:\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Create Engaging Sample Projects\n</b><br>Begin by crafting captivating sample projects that showcase your creativity and skills. Whether it’s mock blog posts that tell an intriguing story, vibrant logos that capture the essence of a brand, or stunning designs that draw the eye, these pieces will serve as your artistic portfolio.\n<br>\n<b><br>Leverage Free or Low-Cost Work\n</b><br>Consider offering your talents for free or at a minimal cost to friends or local businesses. In return, you can request heartfelt testimonials that highlight your expertise and reliability. These endorsements will bolster your credibility and serve as powerful tools in attracting future clients.\n<br>\n<br><b>Showcase Your Work Online\n</b><br>Take the next step by uploading your creations onto platforms like Behance, Medium, or even a shared Google Drive folder. This not only makes your work accessible to potential clients but also allows you to build a digital footprint that showcases your unique style and capabilities.\n<br>\n<br>Step 3: Establish Profiles on Freelance Platforms\n<br>As a novice in the freelancing world, the easiest way to connect with clients is through established online platforms.\n<br>\n<br>Upwork: This platform is ideal for securing higher-paying, long-term contracts, allowing you to cultivate ongoing relationships with clients who appreciate your skill set.\n<br>Fiverr: Perfect for those initial gigs, Fiverr is a fantastic starting point for beginners looking to make their mark in short-term projects.\n<br>LinkedIn: Use this professional network not just for finding jobs, but for networking and attracting inbound leads through your profiles and connections.\n<br>Freelancer.com: Though competitive, this platform offers a plethora of opportunities, making it a great playground for aspiring freelancers to refine their skills.\n<br>Toptal: Designed for highly skilled professionals, Toptal connects you with top-tier clients who are searching for exceptional talent.\n<br>\n<br>By strategically applying these steps, you can navigate the freelancing landscape with confidence and creativity.\n<br>\n<br>👉 Pro Tip: Choose a striking professional profile photo that captures your personality and professionalism. Craft a concise yet captivating bio that reflects your expertise and passion. Emphasize the specific challenges you can address, such as, “I empower small businesses to craft dynamic and engaging social media content, enabling them to amplify their online presence and connect with their audience in meaningful ways.”\n<br>\n<b><br>Step 4: Find Your First Client\n</b><br>This is often the hardest part. Be ready for rejection — most beginners get 20+ “no’s” before a first “yes.”\n<br>\n<br><b>Tips to land that first job:\n</b><br>\n<br>• Craft tailored proposals that reflect the essence of the client’s business, incorporating their name and highlighting their unique offerings.\n<br>• Initially, set your rates strategically lower to draw in potential clients and spark their interest.\n<br>• Go above and beyond in your work—if a client requests 500 words, deliver a polished and refined 550, leaving a lasting impression of your dedication.\n<br>• Gather testimonials to establish a solid foundation of credibility and trustworthiness in your field.\n<br>\n<br><b>Step 5: Get Paid Safely\n</b><br>\n<br>South Africans can use:\n<br>1. Payoneer (popular on Upwork &amp; Fiverr).\n<br>2. Wise (multi-currency accounts).\n<br>3. PayPal (for US/UK clients).\n<br>4. Direct EFT (local clients).\n<br>\n<br>👉 Pro Tip: Always request at least 50% upfront from private clients outside platforms to avoid scams.\n<br>\n<br><b>Building Momentum as a Freelancer\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Once you’ve landed a client or two, here’s how to turn freelancing into a career:\n</b><br>\n<br>• Raise Your Rates Gradually – once you have 5+ good reviews, increase pricing.\n<br>• Specialise in a Niche – specialists charge more (e.g., “Shopify Developer” vs “Web Developer”).\n<br>• Offer Packages – e.g., 10 social media posts/month instead of 1-off posts.\n<br>• Retainers = Stability – aim for clients who pay monthly instead of once-off.\n<br>• Create Passive Income – sell templates, guides, or courses alongside freelancing.\n<br>\n<br><b>Example: How to Earn R10,000/Month as a Freelancer\n</b><br>\n<br>• Writing gigs: 10 blog posts at R1,000 each = R10,000.\n<br>• Virtual assistant: 2 clients at R5,000/month each = R10,000.\n<br>• Design: 5 logos at R2,000 each = R10,000.\n<br>• Mix: 1 international client paying $500 (R9,000) + 2 small local jobs.\n<br>\n<br><b>Challenges to Expect\n</b><br>\n<br>Competition: With thousands of freelancers vying for attention each day, standing out is crucial. **Solution:** Hone in on a specific niche and craft personalized proposals that showcase your unique value and resonate with potential clients.\n<br>Payment Delays: Navigating the often unpredictable nature of freelance payments can be nerve-wracking. To mitigate risks, choose reliable platforms that ensure prompt transactions and establish a buffer fund to cushion against unexpected delays.\n<br>Isolation: The freelance lifestyle can sometimes feel lonely. Combat this sense of isolation by establishing a daily routine that fosters productivity and actively connecting with other freelancers for meaningful support and camaraderie.\n<br>Inconsistent Income: The ebb and flow of freelance income can be challenging. To navigate this rollercoaster, practice diligent budgeting and make the most of high-earning months by saving diligently, ensuring you have a safety net during leaner times.\n<br>\n<br><b>FAQs\n</b><br>\n<br><b>Can I freelance without experience?\n</b><br>Absolutely! Begin your journey with approachable and straightforward tasks such as transcribing audio into text, entering data into spreadsheets, or managing social media accounts. These foundational experiences will provide you with a solid framework, allowing you to gradually expand your skills and knowledge as you progress. Embrace the learning process and elevate your expertise along the way!\n<br>\n<br><b>How long does it take to land a client?\n</b><br>The timeline can span anywhere from a swift two weeks to an extensive three months, influenced significantly by the level of dedication and the specific niche involved.\n<br>\n<br><b>Do I need to register with SARS?\n</b><br>If your freelancing venture provides a steady stream of income, then absolutely! As your business flourishes and gains momentum, consider taking the leap to register as a sole proprietor or even establish a company. This transformation can offer you protection and legitimacy, allowing your creativity to thrive in a more structured environment.\n<br>\n<br><b>How do I balance freelancing with my day job?\n</b><br>Devote 2 to 3 hours each day to your freelancing journey. In South Africa, many aspiring freelancers begin their careers on a part-time basis, gradually building their client base and experience before fully immersing themselves in the world of freelancing. This approach allows for a smooth transition into a rewarding full-time commitment.\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>Freelancing in South Africa has evolved into a vibrant career path, offering more than just a supplementary income—it opens the door to a world of possibilities and significant earning potential. While embarking on this journey requires determination and unwavering perseverance, the rewards can be truly transformative: imagine the freedom to set your own hours, work with clients from across the globe, and potentially craft a thriving business around your unique talents.\n<br>\n<br>Begin your freelancing adventure by honing in on a single skill, selecting one platform to showcase your work, and securing that all-important first client. With patience as your ally and a commitment to continuous learning, you can cultivate a robust freelance career that not only reaches but exceeds R10,000 a month, turning your aspirations into remarkable achievements and endless opportunities.&nbsp;<br></p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
          "_cid": "v5KaOIuZ3N",
          "_anchor": "article12-3e",
          "_protectedParams": [],
          "_global": false,
          "_once": false,
          "_params": {}
        },
        {
          "alias": false,
          "_styles": {
            "padding-top": "(@paddingTop * 1rem)",
            "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 1rem)",
            "& when (@bg-type = 'image')": {
